TOPICS COVERED (PANDAS FOR DATA ANALYSIS & MACHINE LEARNING)
Introduction to Pandas

The training session began with an introduction to Pandas, one of the most widely used Python libraries for data analysis and data manipulation in Artificial Intelligence, Machine Learning, and Data Science. Learned that Pandas provides easy-to-use data structures and functions to organize, clean, analyze, and process large datasets efficiently.

The trainer explained why data preprocessing is an essential step in every Machine Learning project and how Pandas simplifies working with structured data.

Installing and Importing Pandas

Reviewed the installation process of the Pandas library and learned how to import it into Python programs.

Practiced importing the library using:

import pandas as pd

Also revised the use of NumPy alongside Pandas for performing numerical computations.

Understanding Series and DataFrames

Studied the two main data structures provided by Pandas.

Series

Learned that a Series is a one-dimensional labeled array capable of storing data of different types.

Practiced:

Creating Series from lists
Creating Series from dictionaries
Accessing Series elements
Indexing Series

DataFrame

Learned that a DataFrame is a two-dimensional table consisting of rows and columns, similar to an Excel spreadsheet or SQL table.

Practiced:

Creating DataFrames from dictionaries
Creating DataFrames from lists
Viewing DataFrame structure
Reading and Writing Data

Learned how to import datasets from different file formats.

